Description:

Key responsibilities: 
1. Collaborate with other departments to build and improve commercial operation systems. 
In charge of building data system of EU Division, including data collation of historical business and operation, analysis of data warehouse construction; 
Explore the integrated requirements of the customer’s system platform by integrating information from company’s system such as CRM, SCM, SAP, etc. and other daily office software; 
Build a business BI system to automate analysis and prediction of customer’s behavior by developing and constructing analytical tools and models. 
2.E-marketing data operation support 
Explore user research, user behavior analysis and other data business value, help to promote product improvement and operation adjustment; 
Responsible for the demand investigation, data analysis, business analysis and data mining model construction of projects within the department, and analyze customer behavior and customer demand trends; 
Summarize the operation status of business lines and projects, conduct data monitoring, sorting and analysis of daily and promotional marketing activities to provide data support for business decision-making growth; 
Help to investigate, analyze and achieve the tentative data analysis of business department. 
3.Data support for performance management 
Understand commercial team’s needs and work with Finance department to setup correct reporting systems, including BI Sales report, Budget report, Expense report, etc. 
Provide data support for internal management and operation decision-making, help to construct data model; 
Develop and maintain data tools for internal management. 
. Requirements:
 Bachelor degree or above. At least 2 years of data analysis experience, experience in business system development or operation optimization is preferred; 
Familiar with SCM, CRM and BI system, can write data analysis report independently, and be able to find out the reasons for data changes and propose effective solutions; 
Strong data analysis ability and logical thinking ability, have excellent information integration and analysis ability; 
Excellent communication and coordination ability, be good at inter-departmental communication and collaboration with proactive work attitude; 
High English proficiency, English can be used as work language.

Center  Center for Livable Communities 

 Group  Mobility Services 

 Salary Range  $49,441-$84,049 



 POSITION SUMMARY: 
The Atlanta Regional Commission (ARC) is the regional planning and intergovernmental coordination agency that focuses on issues critical to the region’s success, including growth and development, transportation, water resources, services for older adults, and workforce solutions. ARC is dedicated to unifying the region’s collective resources to prepare the metropolitan area for a prosperous future. This is done through professional planning initiatives, the provision of objective information, and the involvement of the community in collaborative partnerships. 
The Atlanta Regional Transportation Demand Management (TDM) Program is managed by ARC’s Mobility Services Group and includes the outreach and marketing efforts of Georgia Commute Options (GCO)*, the regional TDM provider, and seven (7) Transportation Management Associations operating within specific employment centers. The Data Analyst will be responsible for assisting in the successful completion of program evaluation and data analysis related to the Atlanta Regional TDM Program. The Data Analyst will work with internal ARC staff, contractors and consultants in the development of TDM evaluation tools, data analysis, programmatic reports, and commute behavior-related surveys. GCO is a program aimed at helping the region’s employers and property managers develop commute options programs for employees and tenants that enable and encourage commuting by a transportation mode other than a single occupant vehicle as well as incentivizing behavior change in the region’s commuters to carpool, vanpool, transit, bike, walk, and/or telework. 

 ESSENTIAL DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES: 
 Oversee the creation and/or analysis of internally and externally produced data sets in support of the TDM program; 
 Perform analysis and create maps as requested by internal and external program stakeholders, using ArcGIS, Tableau, and other data analysis software; 
 Develop and build evaluation reporting tools for internal and external stakeholders; 
 Create compelling presentations, dashboards and reports which inform the strategies of the Mobility Services Group; 
 Present to program stakeholders (i.e. Georgia Department of Transportation, State Road and Tollway Authority) and other groups on complex data sets and analysis; 
 Assist in the administration of the regional TDM customer relationship management software; 
 Assist in the management and monitoring of program contractors and consultants related to TDM evaluation; 
 Perform other duties as assigned to support agency goals and objectives 

 REQUIRED KNOWLEDGE, SKILLS, ABILITIES AND COMPETENCIES: 
 Knowledge of Transportation Demand Management; 
 Knowledge in collecting and utilizing data to inform and evaluate programs; 
 Ability to maintain a positive team-oriented attitude and to work in a deadline-driven environment; 
 Ability to work independently, in groups and to lead groups; 
 Ability to communicate effectively with internal and external customers, partners and service providers; 
 Ability to work collaboratively with peers whose programs’ success depends on your output; 
 Possess excellent communication, public speaking and presentation skills; 
 Possess advanced writing skills and data analysis; 
 Proficient with Salesforce, ERSI product suite, Tableau, Microsoft Office, Adobe and related software. 

 MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS: 
 Bachelor’s degree in business, economics, statistics, urban planning, computer science, information technology or related field
 One (1) year of data collection and analysis experience and associated technical support, which may include programming 
An equivalent combination of education and experience sufficient to successfully perform the essential duties of the job such as those listed above, unless otherwise subject to any other requirements set forth in law or regulation. 
PREFERRED QUALIFICATION:
 Experience in public policy, planning, data analysis or related field 
SPECIAL REQUIREMENTS: 
 Selected candidate will be required to present documentation of COVID-19 vaccination certification or be required to present a weekly negative COVID test. 
In addition to the detailed examples of responsibilities and abilities contained herein, all employees of the Atlanta Regional Commission are expected to model behavior consistent with the guiding principles outlined in our  Evolution Strategy . Specifically, incumbents are responsible for demonstrating work habits that are: 
 Interdisciplinary by promoting professional and interpersonal connections and integration across functional disciplines; 
 Holistic by seeking expertise within the team, Group, or Agency to produce his/her work output, and demonstrating a strong understanding of and support for interrelationships between their work and the work of others in the team, Group, or Agency; 
 Actionable by continuously striving to improve his/her capabilities to produce sustainable outcomes, and displaying a strong need for achievement and a high energy level to attain goals; 
 Outcome Based by taking the initiative to meet goals and expectations, and consistently striving to produce tangible results with significant visible impact, and; 
 Targeted toward Ensuring Colleagues' Success by willingly and deliberately providing his/her expertise to others in an effort to build and sustain effective internal and external working relationships, and by modeling behaviors that consistently demonstrate concern for colleagues' success, needs, respect, trust and integrity.

Location: Adelphi, MD (remote until further notice) 
HelioCampus is an analytics platform-as-a-service company serving higher education institutions throughout the US. We offer a secure cloud-based platform that includes flexible data models, best-in-class visual analytics, and expert analysis to enable higher education leaders to make more informed decisions. 
We are seeking a Data Analyst to join our team of higher education data experts. The analyst will work closely with other team members and clients to understand their reporting and analytical needs, evaluate processes and help deploy data solutions in production. The ideal candidate will possess both strong technical ability as well as effective communication and collaboration skills. 
Specific responsibilities are as follows: 
Leverage SQL and other enterprise business intelligence query tools to develop reports and dashboards. 
Perform quantitative analyses to find causality that would result in actionable recommendations to support management decision making. 
Deploy data products in the data warehouse, complete data validation and facilitate end user testing on designed reports and data products. 
Develop subject matter expertise in the HelioCampus data platform and guide stakeholders in the use of the platform to answer strategic institutional questions. 
Required Experience: 
Bachelor’s degree from an accredited institution of higher learning; 
Experience working with relational databases; 
Strong knowledge of SQL, and/or R/ Python queries to build reports and answer ad hoc questions; 
Expertise leveraging Excel and data visualization tools such as Tableau to manipulate, analyze and present data; 
Excellent communication skills and experience presenting findings to stakeholders; 
Ability to work effectively on multiple priorities with strict deliverable dates; 
. 
Preferred Experience: 
Bachelor’s degree with two year of experience or a Master’s degree in any quantitative filed; 
One year or more professional experience in analytics and reporting using SQL, R/Python; 
Experience performing statistical analysis to identify trends, establish patterns and relationships in data to provide answers to questions posed by others; 
Compensation and Benefits: 
Competitive salary, based on experience 
Comprehensive benefits package includes medical, dental, life and disability insurance 
401K with company match 
5+ weeks of paid time off including holidays and vacation 
Work with the smartest and most driven coworkers in the industry 
We are an equal opportunity employer and value diversity at our company. We do not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, color, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, age, marital status, veteran status, or disability status.

