Colgate is seeking qualified candidates for the position of Data Analyst, FI. This position will build models of data that enable the implementation of the Financial Business KPIs and produce an inventory of the data needed to realize the Finance Analytics vision. Specific responsibilities will include but are not limited to the following: 
Design, develop, and maintain a global data warehouse and analytics architecture to enable self service business analysis, reporting needs, and data science initiatives; 
Define how the data is stored, consumed, coordinated and led by different data entities and IT systems; 
Engage with the data warehousing team in the migration to cloud warehousing; 
Design and develop data marts for consumption by analytics tools and end users; 
Participate in the development and maintenance of ETL jobs and data pipelines to aggregate data from various on premise, cloud platforms & external data sources; 
Build expertise in diverse and emerging technologies and new architectural concepts and principles. 
Develop SMART action plans and require minimal supervision during execution; 
Communicate with stakeholders to understand current needs, near-term plans, and opportunities for improved data-driven decision support; 
Write custom SQL queries to extract data from internal databases; 
Write python scripts to perform descriptive statistical analysis of data to meet stakeholder needs; 
Write ABAP code to support development needs or to fix issues; 
Share knowledge with immediate Finance team through regular presentations of progress, struggles, and advances. 
Position Requirements: 
Bachelor's degree required in Computer Science, Statistics, or Management Information Systems; 
2 or more years of programming experience; 
Skills in Python and Java 
Proficiency with SQL implementations; 
Excellent oral and written communication skills 
Preferred Requirements: 
At least 1 year of prior experience with data pipelines and streaming frameworks such as Pubsub, Spark, Airflow, Kafka, etc.; 
Skills in Snowflake, Bigquery 
Finance background for an understanding of basic financial concepts; 
Skills/experience in ABAP 
